<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,251]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</emphasis>
Morphologically similar to 
<emphasis box="[641,764,153,178]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1876" box="[641,761,153,178]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catoirei">P. catoirei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
distinguished by the dark black lateral margin of the pronotum, dark brown tibia, convex elytra with reddish brown scutellum, narrow median transverse band, obliterate humerus, and the apical border of the elytra, which covers the striations as well as intervals.
</paragraph>
